1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:03,268
Julia:
<i>Chester's mill is a place</i>
<i>like any other.</i>

2
00:00:03,270 --> 00:00:05,270
<i>At least it used to be</i>

3
00:00:05,272 --> 00:00:07,272
<i>Until we were cut off</i>
<i>from the rest of the world</i>

4
00:00:07,274 --> 00:00:09,174
<i>By a mysterious dome.</i>

5
00:00:12,780 --> 00:00:15,514
<i>Invisible, indestructible,</i>

6
00:00:15,516 --> 00:00:17,182
<i>And completely inescapable.</i>

7
00:00:17,184 --> 00:00:19,184
We're trapped.

8
00:00:19,186 --> 00:00:21,720
Julia:
<i>We don't know where it</i>
<i>came from or why it's here,</i>

9
00:00:21,722 --> 00:00:24,156
<i>But now trapped under</i>
<i>the dome together,</i>

10
00:00:24,158 --> 00:00:25,758
<i>None of our secrets are safe.</i>

11
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:27,459
It's the pink stars.

12
00:00:27,461 --> 00:00:30,062
Joe:
And they're making
constellations.

13
00:00:30,064 --> 00:00:32,464
What does it mean?

14
00:00:32,466 --> 00:00:34,166
Julia:
<i>Peter got in over his head</i>

15
00:00:34,168 --> 00:00:37,770
<i>And forced you to kill him</i>
<i>to defend yourself.</i>

16
00:00:37,772 --> 00:00:40,172
I found this life
insurance policy today.

17
00:00:40,174 --> 00:00:41,573
This would be void

18
00:00:41,575 --> 00:00:46,311
Hello, max.
For the past eight days,
I've been watching you.

19
00:00:46,313 --> 00:00:48,480
<i>Anything bad happens to me,</i>

20
00:00:48,482 --> 00:00:49,715
Your secrets still come out.

21
00:00:49,717 --> 00:00:51,717
Agatha:
That's my daughter maxine.

22
00:00:51,719 --> 00:00:54,153
Now, do me a favor
and drop that gun.

23
00:00:54,788 --> 00:00:56,422
agatha!

24
00:00:57,390 --> 00:00:58,557
Please.

25
00:01:01,828 --> 00:01:03,529
Junior:
It's amazing.

26
00:01:03,531 --> 00:01:06,465
It's still just
a barn, galileo.

27
00:01:06,467 --> 00:01:09,334
Angie:
Great, so we painted dots over
those lights from the egg.

28
00:01:09,336 --> 00:01:11,103
What does it mean?

29
00:01:11,105 --> 00:01:14,740
Maybe the dome's
trying to communicate.

30
00:01:14,742 --> 00:01:17,709
It stopped the riots
with the rain.

31
00:01:17,711 --> 00:01:19,745
Made us babble about pink stars.

32
00:01:19,747 --> 00:01:23,549
I wonder what it's
trying to tell us now.

33
00:01:27,153 --> 00:01:29,588
I don't know.

34
00:01:29,590 --> 00:01:32,691
But these four stars aren't

35
00:01:32,693 --> 00:01:34,593
Part of any constellation.

36
00:01:34,595 --> 00:01:36,428
I think they're us.

37
00:01:36,430 --> 00:01:38,430
Junior:
What's this guy

38
00:01:38,432 --> 00:01:40,499
Have to do with it?

39
00:01:42,702 --> 00:01:44,670
Hey, it changed
color overnight.

40
00:01:44,672 --> 00:01:47,339
From green to clear.

41
00:01:47,341 --> 00:01:49,475
You can see wings now.

42
00:01:49,477 --> 00:01:51,110
It's a monarch.

43
00:01:51,112 --> 00:01:53,112
It's gonna hatch
into a butterfly.

44
00:01:53,114 --> 00:01:54,780
It's pretty rad.

45
00:01:54,782 --> 00:01:56,582
It's not rad...
It's insane!

46
00:01:56,584 --> 00:01:58,750
We're, like,
the guardians

47
00:01:58,752 --> 00:02:00,752
Of some secret cosmic mystery.

48
00:02:02,656 --> 00:02:04,823
It's too much, it's too much.

49
00:02:06,659 --> 00:02:08,660
We've got to tell somebody.

50
00:02:08,662 --> 00:02:10,496
The dome's been
pretty clear

51
00:02:10,498 --> 00:02:12,564
About not wanting anyone else
to know about it.

52
00:02:12,566 --> 00:02:13,765
When dodee snuck in here,

53
00:02:13,767 --> 00:02:15,734
She got zapped
and wound up in the hospital.

54
00:02:16,736 --> 00:02:19,238
We could tell julia.

55
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:21,306
When she touched
this thing,

56
00:02:21,308 --> 00:02:24,543
She said my ghost told her that
the monarch will be crowned.

57
00:02:24,545 --> 00:02:26,545
Maybe she's not one of us,

58
00:02:26,547 --> 00:02:28,280
But she might have some answers.

59
00:02:28,282 --> 00:02:29,548
Junior:
He's right.

60
00:02:29,550 --> 00:02:32,151
That thing's gonna hatch,

61
00:02:32,153 --> 00:02:33,318
And when it does,

62
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:35,821
Maybe it will...
Lead us to something.

63
00:02:35,823 --> 00:02:37,556
Or someone.

64
00:02:37,558 --> 00:02:39,825
Like the monarch's a person.

65
00:02:41,261 --> 00:02:42,828
Like a king maybe.

66
00:02:42,830 --> 00:02:44,429
Who might be able
to bring the dome down.

67
00:02:44,431 --> 00:02:45,831
All right.

68
00:02:45,833 --> 00:02:49,301
So the dome trusts julia.

69
00:02:49,303 --> 00:02:50,936
Joe, go tell her.

70
00:03:01,414 --> 00:03:03,549
I just want to make sure
that we're on the same page.

71
00:03:03,551 --> 00:03:06,485
So, you, duke perkins and
reverend coggins conspired

72
00:03:06,487 --> 00:03:08,620
To acquire a vast
amount of propane?

73
00:03:08,622 --> 00:03:10,656
Yeah, we bought propane
off the books.

74
00:03:10,658 --> 00:03:13,458
But only to keep
this town afloat.

75
00:03:13,460 --> 00:03:15,961
By selling it to
maxine seagrave?

76
00:03:15,963 --> 00:03:17,429
A drug dealer?

77
00:03:17,431 --> 00:03:19,331
But you kept some of
it in your warehouse.

78
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:21,767
And you can thank
the lord that we did.

79
00:03:21,769 --> 00:03:24,836
Because right now
in the middle of this...

80
00:03:24,838 --> 00:03:28,640
Nightmare,
the lights are on.

81
00:03:28,642 --> 00:03:31,376
Because your generator
is running

82
00:03:31,378 --> 00:03:32,844
Using my propane.

83
00:03:32,846 --> 00:03:35,380
The diner's open
because of my propane.

84
00:03:35,382 --> 00:03:38,617
We're setting up irrigation
for crops, bartering systems.

85
00:03:38,619 --> 00:03:41,420
Hell, chester's mill
might just stay alive

86
00:03:41,422 --> 00:03:43,755
Because of my propane.

87
00:03:45,758 --> 00:03:47,893
You think I'm a crook?

88
00:03:49,396 --> 00:03:50,762
I think I'm owed a damn parade.

89
00:03:50,764 --> 00:03:52,231
You know, it
doesn't change

90
00:03:52,233 --> 00:03:54,399
The fact that if this dome
hadn't come down,

91
00:03:54,401 --> 00:03:57,236
You'd be in jail.

92
00:03:57,238 --> 00:04:00,005
I'd say it saved
your ass, big jim.

93
00:04:00,007 --> 00:04:03,375
So, go ahead.

94
00:04:03,377 --> 00:04:07,312
Charge me with conspiracy
to keep the lights on.

95
00:04:08,648 --> 00:04:09,715
Or...

96
00:04:11,651 --> 00:04:14,253
...You can go after
a real criminal.

97
00:04:14,255 --> 00:04:16,655
And who might that be?

98
00:04:16,657 --> 00:04:17,889
Someone who's
a real mystery

99
00:04:17,891 --> 00:04:19,691
In this town.

100
00:04:19,693 --> 00:04:21,660
A man who just got here.

101
00:04:21,662 --> 00:04:24,930
Who's only out
for himself.

102
00:04:24,932 --> 00:04:27,532
And isn't shy about...

103
00:04:27,534 --> 00:04:30,035
Letting people know it.

104
00:04:39,545 --> 00:04:42,681
How was the couch?

105
00:04:42,683 --> 00:04:46,551
Lonely.

106
00:04:46,553 --> 00:04:49,354
So was the bed.

107
00:04:49,356 --> 00:04:51,356
Do you want me to leave?

108
00:04:52,825 --> 00:04:55,560
I want you to take me
to peter's grave.

109
00:04:57,730 --> 00:04:59,998
For us to move forward,

110
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,733
I need closure.

111
00:05:01,735 --> 00:05:02,968
I think you do, too.

112
00:05:02,970 --> 00:05:05,304
So...

113
00:05:05,306 --> 00:05:09,308
Yeah, I need
to see peter's grave.

114
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:23,555
I'll go get dressed.

115
00:05:29,829 --> 00:05:31,830
Linda:
You want me to go after barbie?

116
00:05:31,832 --> 00:05:32,964
What did he ever do?

117
00:05:32,966 --> 00:05:37,469
Barbie wasn't just passing
through chester's mill.

118
00:05:37,471 --> 00:05:40,072
He was here,
working for max seagrave.

119
00:05:40,074 --> 00:05:41,073
He was?

120
00:05:41,075 --> 00:05:42,541
That's her gambling
enforcer.

121
00:05:42,543 --> 00:05:44,009
He was here
putting the screws

122
00:05:44,011 --> 00:05:46,611
To people in this town--
our town.

123
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:49,848
No, this sounds...

124
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:52,517
Crazy? Till it's true.

125
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:54,019
Here's a name
you haven't heard in a while.

126
00:05:54,021 --> 00:05:55,487
Peter shumway.

127
00:05:55,489 --> 00:05:58,023
He was up to his eyeballs
in debt to max.

128
00:05:58,025 --> 00:06:00,092
Barbie was with him
the day the dome came down.

129
00:06:00,094 --> 00:06:01,927
And guess what?

130
00:06:01,929 --> 00:06:05,130
Haven't heard a peep
from old peter since.

131
00:06:11,471 --> 00:06:14,840
You know,
some people have secrets you...

132
00:06:14,842 --> 00:06:16,742
You couldn't imagine.

133
00:06:20,446 --> 00:06:22,080
What about you?

134
00:06:22,082 --> 00:06:24,583
I'm an open book.

135
00:06:27,587 --> 00:06:29,654
I got it.

136
00:06:33,426 --> 00:06:35,861
Can I help you?

137
00:06:35,863 --> 00:06:38,497
Right now,
you can't even help yourself.

138
00:07:02,989 --> 00:07:05,791
Julia!

139
00:07:05,793 --> 00:07:07,726
Hold on.

140
00:07:09,061 --> 00:07:10,595
Linda, are you there?

141
00:07:10,597 --> 00:07:11,763
Linda:
I'm here, barbie.

142
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:12,864
Julia's been shot!

143
00:07:12,866 --> 00:07:14,966
What?
She answered the door

144
00:07:14,968 --> 00:07:16,668
And somebody shot her.
Who?

145
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:17,736
I don't know!

146
00:07:18,538 --> 00:07:19,938
If you can believe him.

147
00:07:23,676 --> 00:07:25,744
Linda, listen,
I can't drive

148
00:07:25,746 --> 00:07:27,846
And keep her from bleeding out
at the same time.

149
00:07:27,848 --> 00:07:29,214
I need someone
to give me a ride right now.

150
00:07:29,216 --> 00:07:30,715
I'll be right there, barbie.

151
00:07:30,717 --> 00:07:34,553
Linda... Think.

152
00:07:34,555 --> 00:07:36,721
Think.

153
00:07:41,194 --> 00:07:43,028
You hungry?

154
00:07:43,030 --> 00:07:44,229
Yeah.

155
00:07:44,231 --> 00:07:46,031
Well, our chickens
are still laying eggs.

156
00:07:46,033 --> 00:07:48,099
I can scramble some up.

157
00:07:50,903 --> 00:07:52,838
Can you believe it, angie?

158
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:55,574
Uh, no, it's...

159
00:07:55,576 --> 00:07:58,677
All been pretty crazy.

160
00:07:58,679 --> 00:08:00,178
I mean us.

161
00:08:01,714 --> 00:08:05,650
I... I, uh...

162
00:08:05,652 --> 00:08:07,519
I never thought
fate was real.

163
00:08:07,521 --> 00:08:10,489
That there was this...

164
00:08:10,491 --> 00:08:13,058
Plan.

165
00:08:13,060 --> 00:08:14,659
But now it's undeniable.

166
00:08:14,661 --> 00:08:16,561
What are you talking about?

167
00:08:16,563 --> 00:08:17,762
The way our lives are
braided together.

168
00:08:17,764 --> 00:08:19,998
And they will be forever.

169
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,101
What? Are you insane?!

170
00:08:23,103 --> 00:08:25,070
You kept me prisoner, okay?

171
00:08:25,072 --> 00:08:26,538
I almost died down there!

172
00:08:26,540 --> 00:08:28,673
But you didn't.

173
00:08:28,675 --> 00:08:31,676
We're both alive
and we're here right now.

174
00:08:31,678 --> 00:08:33,778
It is the four of us
who are connected.

175
00:08:33,780 --> 00:08:35,780
It is not about you and me.

176
00:08:35,782 --> 00:08:37,249
It will never be about you...

177
00:08:37,251 --> 00:08:38,984
I don't believe you.
Well, believe it!

178
00:08:38,986 --> 00:08:41,586
We will never be together!

179
00:08:41,588 --> 00:08:44,222
And if somehow
we make this dome come down,

180
00:08:44,224 --> 00:08:45,757
Then I am gone, too.

181
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:50,795
And you will never see me again.

182
00:08:51,797 --> 00:08:54,232
Then I'm out.

183
00:08:54,234 --> 00:08:56,067
What?

184
00:08:56,069 --> 00:08:57,569
I'm done with you, with this,

185
00:08:57,571 --> 00:08:59,204
The mini-dome, all of it.

186
00:08:59,206 --> 00:09:00,539
You can't just walk out.

187
00:09:00,541 --> 00:09:01,740
We need your...
My hand?

188
00:09:01,742 --> 00:09:03,708
I know...
My hand on the little dome

189
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:04,976
So we can make pink stars and do

190
00:09:04,978 --> 00:09:06,578
Whatever the hell else
it wants to do.

191
00:09:06,580 --> 00:09:08,847
This might be our only shot.

192
00:09:08,849 --> 00:09:11,850
and you're gonna
ruin that out of spite?

193
00:09:13,687 --> 00:09:15,787
I've never met someone
so selfish!

194
00:09:20,293 --> 00:09:22,093
It's love, angie.

195
00:09:22,095 --> 00:09:24,329
I'd rather live in here

196
00:09:24,331 --> 00:09:27,232
And die in here
than be apart from you.

197
00:09:40,112 --> 00:09:41,947
Damn it!

198
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:47,152
Great.

199
00:09:47,154 --> 00:09:49,621
Now even the cops
are getting ripped off.

200
00:09:49,623 --> 00:09:51,222
I need a ride!

201
00:09:51,224 --> 00:09:52,891
No gas.

202
00:09:57,096 --> 00:09:58,863
Stop your vehicle!

203
00:10:02,134 --> 00:10:03,134
What, are you carjacking me?

204
00:10:03,136 --> 00:10:04,169
Phil, I need a ride
to julia's.

205
00:10:04,171 --> 00:10:05,737
She just got shot.

206
00:10:05,739 --> 00:10:07,639
Get in.

207
00:10:12,378 --> 00:10:13,945
Joe!
Barbie?

208
00:10:13,947 --> 00:10:15,847
Hey, get in here right now!

209
00:10:15,849 --> 00:10:17,983
Oh, my god.

210
00:10:17,985 --> 00:10:20,151
Uh, yeah. I have
my learner's permit,

211
00:10:20,153 --> 00:10:21,853
But the guy said
I didn't check my mirrors.

212
00:10:21,855 --> 00:10:23,154
Just help-help me get her
in the car.

213
00:10:23,156 --> 00:10:26,057
Now come on. Sit her up.
Let's go. Sit her up.

214
00:10:28,394 --> 00:10:30,261
Get the door! Get the door!

215
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:45,877
Are we good?

216
00:10:45,879 --> 00:10:47,145
Yeah, we're good. Go!

217
00:11:04,096 --> 00:11:05,964
What the hell?

218
00:11:05,966 --> 00:11:07,866
Hell's down here.

219
00:11:07,868 --> 00:11:09,067
You want a ride?

220
00:11:09,069 --> 00:11:12,337
You just happen
to be in the neighborhood?

221
00:11:13,806 --> 00:11:17,142
It'll be nice to get
a little bit of rain.

222
00:11:21,414 --> 00:11:22,981
You and I need to talk.

223
00:11:26,252 --> 00:11:28,887
Somebody shot
julia shumway.

224
00:11:28,889 --> 00:11:31,690
It's a perilous
world we live in.

225
00:11:34,293 --> 00:11:36,194
I know it was you.

226
00:11:36,196 --> 00:11:41,466
Well, barbie said the one word
a girl hates to hear: "no."

227
00:11:41,468 --> 00:11:43,334
Where is this going, max?

228
00:11:43,336 --> 00:11:44,803
That's up to you,
jimmy.

229
00:11:44,805 --> 00:11:47,138
Life's all about making
the right choices.

230
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:49,007
You make the right one,
you play nice,

231
00:11:49,009 --> 00:11:50,275
And it's good between us.

232
00:11:50,277 --> 00:11:52,110
You step out of line
like barbie did...?

233
00:11:52,112 --> 00:11:53,745
Lucky for me I'm single.

234
00:11:53,747 --> 00:11:56,114
Oh, I'm sure there's someone
around here you care about.

235
00:11:56,116 --> 00:11:57,248
Junior:
Dad.

236
00:12:00,486 --> 00:12:02,353
Go on to work, junior.

237
00:12:02,355 --> 00:12:05,056
Well, look who
I <i>finally</i> get to meet.

238
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:06,091
Junior, hi.
Hi.

239
00:12:06,093 --> 00:12:08,159
I'm a friend
of your dad's.

240
00:12:08,161 --> 00:12:09,427
Hi.

241
00:12:09,429 --> 00:12:12,230
Wow, you are,
you're a rennie, all right.

242
00:12:12,232 --> 00:12:15,967
Those eyes, it's, like...
It's like I'm looking

243
00:12:15,969 --> 00:12:17,235
Right at your mom.

244
00:12:17,237 --> 00:12:19,437
I bet you face
a lot of danger

245
00:12:19,439 --> 00:12:24,075
And I bet your dad is
just constantly worried
about you, huh?

246
00:12:25,077 --> 00:12:26,311
All right, that's enough, max.

247
00:12:26,313 --> 00:12:29,948
I have some business
to attend to on bird island.

248
00:12:29,950 --> 00:12:32,217
The weather's acting up.

249
00:12:32,219 --> 00:12:35,120
I'm not sure it's a great
time to be on the water.

250
00:12:35,122 --> 00:12:36,788
Aren't you sweet
to think about me?

251
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:39,324
Your dad, he is so
thoughtful, to the end.

252
00:12:39,326 --> 00:12:41,192
I'll be at the factory
later on

253
00:12:41,194 --> 00:12:42,827
If you need me.

254
00:12:42,829 --> 00:12:45,130
Ciao.

255
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:56,875
Who was that?

256
00:12:57,810 --> 00:12:59,511
The devil.

257
00:13:09,823 --> 00:13:12,257
Julia! Jul, hey, hey, hey,
stay with me.

258
00:13:12,259 --> 00:13:14,159
Hey, you got to hurry, joe.
She's crashing!

259
00:13:14,161 --> 00:13:15,527
I'm working on it.

260
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:23,368
You're doing great, joe.
Just get us there.

261
00:13:24,970 --> 00:13:26,838
It's pretty bad up there.

262
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:29,974
Yeah, it's pretty bad
back here, too, joe.

263
00:13:29,976 --> 00:13:31,242
I mean, it's not just
the weather.

264
00:13:31,244 --> 00:13:32,377
It's the dome.

265
00:13:32,379 --> 00:13:34,379
I think it's
angry at us.

266
00:13:47,961 --> 00:13:49,127
I got julia.

267
00:13:49,129 --> 00:13:50,895
You pop the trunk,
plug this thing in.

268
00:13:50,897 --> 00:13:52,530
We need the juice.
Okay.

269
00:14:13,152 --> 00:14:14,352
Barbie!

270
00:14:16,155 --> 00:14:19,157
All right, let's get
her inside!

271
00:14:19,159 --> 00:14:21,092
Put her in the
second room.

272
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:23,862
Yeah, right there.

273
00:14:23,864 --> 00:14:24,996
So, it's a through
and through?

274
00:14:24,998 --> 00:14:26,231
Then there's no
bullet to remove?

275
00:14:26,233 --> 00:14:29,400
Sounds like she's taking in air
through the wound,

276
00:14:29,402 --> 00:14:30,969
So we've got to relieve
this pressure,

277
00:14:30,971 --> 00:14:32,604
Or else it's gonna
crush her heart and lungs.

278
00:14:32,606 --> 00:14:35,406
Please, somebody,
a tree fell on our garage!

279
00:14:35,408 --> 00:14:36,941
My husband was inside!

280
00:14:36,943 --> 00:14:38,476
He's not breathing!

281
00:14:41,348 --> 00:14:43,348
Go get me a piece
of plastic tubing

282
00:14:43,350 --> 00:14:46,017
So we can relieve the
pressure in her chest here.

283
00:14:48,587 --> 00:14:50,989
This place is picked clean.

284
00:14:50,991 --> 00:14:53,124
I'll make do with a pen,
plastic bag.

285
00:14:53,126 --> 00:14:54,225
Grab some alcohol.

286
00:14:57,529 --> 00:14:59,397
Pen, plastic bag,
the alcohol.

287
00:14:59,399 --> 00:15:01,499
How do you know
how to do all this?

288
00:15:01,501 --> 00:15:04,502
I had to chest tube
my team sergeant in fallujah.

289
00:15:04,504 --> 00:15:06,137
What happened to him?

290
00:15:28,928 --> 00:15:31,229
I thought everybody had
to turn in their guns.

291
00:15:31,231 --> 00:15:32,964
I'm not everybody.

292
00:15:36,268 --> 00:15:38,703
Dad, what's going on?

293
00:15:38,705 --> 00:15:41,239
That woman max...

294
00:15:41,241 --> 00:15:45,209
She's gonna take everything
I worked for...

295
00:15:45,211 --> 00:15:47,111
And destroy it.

296
00:15:47,113 --> 00:15:49,247
What do you mean?

297
00:15:49,249 --> 00:15:51,649
Son, I've been doing my damndest

298
00:15:51,651 --> 00:15:54,519
To get things back to normal,

299
00:15:54,521 --> 00:15:56,254
Make the trains run on time.

300
00:15:56,256 --> 00:16:00,024
Max is trying
to fill those trains

301
00:16:00,026 --> 00:16:02,026
With drugs and liquor
and every kind of sick vice

302
00:16:02,028 --> 00:16:03,294
Human beings can get into.

303
00:16:03,296 --> 00:16:05,263
She seems nice enough to me.

304
00:16:05,265 --> 00:16:06,698
Well, that just

305
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:09,000
Shows you don't know what
the hell you're talking about.

306
00:16:18,177 --> 00:16:21,312
She's angry, junior...

307
00:16:21,314 --> 00:16:22,714
At me.

308
00:16:25,017 --> 00:16:28,086
And she wants to hurt me...

309
00:16:28,088 --> 00:16:30,755
By hurting you.

310
00:16:33,592 --> 00:16:35,093
Then let me help you.

311
00:16:36,996 --> 00:16:38,329
I can handle this.

312
00:16:38,331 --> 00:16:39,664
Dad, I can help.
Junior, no.

313
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:41,199
I'm a man.
No, I can do something!
Junior.

314
00:16:41,201 --> 00:16:43,101
Junior, no!

315
00:16:53,212 --> 00:16:55,246
Single dad...

316
00:16:57,249 --> 00:16:59,417
...Raising a kid.

317
00:17:04,356 --> 00:17:08,226
I did the best I could.

318
00:17:08,228 --> 00:17:11,029
But you still punish me for it.

319
00:17:11,031 --> 00:17:12,130
I know I have,

320
00:17:12,132 --> 00:17:15,400
But not anymore.

321
00:17:17,036 --> 00:17:19,404
Look, son, with someone
like max...

322
00:17:20,372 --> 00:17:22,573
...I don't know how this ends.

323
00:17:22,575 --> 00:17:24,242
Dad, don't say that.

324
00:17:24,244 --> 00:17:25,777
It's the truth.

325
00:17:39,625 --> 00:17:42,093
You stay in the house.

326
00:17:42,095 --> 00:17:46,164
Do not open the door
for anybody but me.

327
00:17:46,166 --> 00:17:48,533
Do you hear me?

328
00:17:59,179 --> 00:18:01,412
Lightning.

329
00:18:01,414 --> 00:18:03,581
I wonder if that changes
anything.

330
00:18:07,152 --> 00:18:08,486
Okay.

331
00:18:11,590 --> 00:18:13,357
Man:
Imagery transmission.

332
00:18:13,359 --> 00:18:15,560
Uhf data adapter.

333
00:18:15,562 --> 00:18:17,261
Satcom.

334
00:18:17,263 --> 00:18:19,664
You're kidding me.
It's working again.

335
00:18:19,666 --> 00:18:21,332
All right, come on, baby.

336
00:18:21,334 --> 00:18:22,366
Speak clearly.

337
00:18:22,368 --> 00:18:23,501
Affirm.

338
00:18:23,503 --> 00:18:24,869
Man 2:
It's barbie. We've confirmed it.

339
00:18:24,871 --> 00:18:26,504
Barbie?

340
00:18:26,506 --> 00:18:27,772
Man 1:
Yes, sir.

341
00:18:27,774 --> 00:18:29,540
We reviewed the tape
from visitors' day.

342
00:18:29,542 --> 00:18:32,810
There's no question--
that's dale barbara in there.

343
00:18:32,812 --> 00:18:36,180
Man 2:
Roger that. He's the one
we've been looking for.

344
00:19:03,175 --> 00:19:04,575
What the hell are you doing?!

345
00:19:04,577 --> 00:19:06,377
I could ask you
the same thing.

346
00:19:06,379 --> 00:19:08,146
Well, don't bother shooting me!

347
00:19:08,148 --> 00:19:09,780
You're about to get
the whole town killed!

348
00:19:09,782 --> 00:19:11,182
What?

349
00:19:11,184 --> 00:19:13,818
Junior, look at what
it's doing!

350
00:19:15,721 --> 00:19:16,854
What is that?

351
00:19:16,856 --> 00:19:18,723
it's sending a message.

352
00:19:18,725 --> 00:19:20,892
You have to come back
to the group.

353
00:19:20,894 --> 00:19:23,594
It takes all of us,
or we're nothing!

354
00:19:23,596 --> 00:19:26,364
It's talking to us, junior.
To you!

355
00:19:26,366 --> 00:19:28,566
What, so now I control
the weather?

356
00:19:29,935 --> 00:19:32,470
This thing has done
a lot of crazy stuff,

357
00:19:32,472 --> 00:19:33,905
But never this.

358
00:19:33,907 --> 00:19:36,641
Not until you turned
your back on us.

359
00:19:50,355 --> 00:19:51,889
Barbie?

360
00:19:56,261 --> 00:19:58,529
I'm okay.

361
00:20:02,334 --> 00:20:03,334
What's happening?

362
00:20:03,336 --> 00:20:04,602
Her heart stopped.

363
00:20:04,604 --> 00:20:06,204
Too much pressure.

364
00:20:12,212 --> 00:20:13,211
Uh...

365
00:20:16,248 --> 00:20:17,315
What are you doing?

366
00:20:17,317 --> 00:20:18,616
I'm sucking out

367
00:20:18,618 --> 00:20:20,318
The extra air
in her chest.

368
00:20:30,395 --> 00:20:31,629
Junior:
Come on, we
gotta ride it out

369
00:20:31,631 --> 00:20:33,297
Down in the shelter!
No, are you nuts?!

370
00:20:33,299 --> 00:20:34,932
We have to go be
with joe and norrie!

371
00:20:34,934 --> 00:20:36,467
My dad said to stay here.

372
00:20:36,469 --> 00:20:38,936
Junior, do you want
to make this right?

373
00:20:38,938 --> 00:20:40,538
Then come
with me.

374
00:20:40,540 --> 00:20:42,907
Not because
I am promising you anything,

375
00:20:42,909 --> 00:20:44,976
But because the dome
is telling you

376
00:20:44,978 --> 00:20:47,411
What you're supposed to do
to be with us.

377
00:20:48,780 --> 00:20:50,348
We need you.

378
00:20:50,350 --> 00:20:52,550
<i>You</i> need me, angie.

379
00:20:53,518 --> 00:20:55,419
Fine.

380
00:20:55,421 --> 00:20:57,255
I need you.

381
00:20:57,257 --> 00:20:58,956
Now come on!

382
00:20:58,958 --> 00:21:00,858
Come on,
we gotta go, come on!

383
00:21:03,462 --> 00:21:04,629
Angie!

384
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:22,747
See?

385
00:21:25,284 --> 00:21:26,684
I was right!

386
00:22:02,487 --> 00:22:04,555
It worked.

387
00:22:08,894 --> 00:22:11,062
You did it.

388
00:22:12,531 --> 00:22:14,465
I had a little help, joe.

389
00:22:24,643 --> 00:22:26,477
Joe:
Storm's breaking up.

390
00:22:27,713 --> 00:22:28,979
I gotta go now.

391
00:22:29,948 --> 00:22:32,416
I have to tell them.

392
00:22:32,418 --> 00:22:34,051
You have to tell who?

393
00:22:34,053 --> 00:22:35,886
You saved julia.

394
00:22:35,888 --> 00:22:38,422
Just like you saved me
when the dome came down.

395
00:22:40,726 --> 00:22:43,861
Maybe you're here
to save all of us.

396
00:22:45,630 --> 00:22:47,531
I don't think so, bud.

397
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:48,799
Junior was right.

398
00:22:48,801 --> 00:22:50,134
The monarch's a person.

399
00:22:52,671 --> 00:22:55,806
That person's you.

400
00:23:11,523 --> 00:23:13,591
♪

401
00:23:42,621 --> 00:23:44,088
Oh, mom.

402
00:24:21,626 --> 00:24:23,661
Barbie:
Hey, listen.

403
00:24:23,663 --> 00:24:25,062
I don't want to leave her,
but I gotta go

404
00:24:25,064 --> 00:24:26,764
Take care of something,
so could you...

405
00:24:26,766 --> 00:24:27,998
She and I
aren't going anywhere.

406
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:30,501
Thank you.

407
00:24:44,015 --> 00:24:45,749
Julia okay?

408
00:24:45,751 --> 00:24:47,952
Barely.

409
00:24:53,758 --> 00:24:55,793
Still...

410
00:24:55,795 --> 00:24:58,195
You know it's max
who shot her, right?

411
00:24:59,164 --> 00:25:00,931
Yeah.

412
00:25:00,933 --> 00:25:01,932
And I also know

413
00:25:01,934 --> 00:25:03,200
That it's time
to stop her.

414
00:25:04,703 --> 00:25:06,904
It's gonna take both of us
to do it.

415
00:25:10,275 --> 00:25:13,677
But we're gonna do this
by my rules, jim.

416
00:25:13,679 --> 00:25:15,079
We're taking max alive.

417
00:25:15,081 --> 00:25:16,080
Oh, great.

418
00:25:16,082 --> 00:25:18,549
So we'll be high and mighty...

419
00:25:18,551 --> 00:25:19,817
And dead.

420
00:25:19,819 --> 00:25:21,552
That's all you know, isn't it?

421
00:25:21,554 --> 00:25:23,153
Kill or be killed?

422
00:25:24,222 --> 00:25:25,890
You're not saving
chester's mill,

423
00:25:25,892 --> 00:25:27,725
You're eating
this town alive.

424
00:25:27,727 --> 00:25:29,760
You have no idea
what it takes.
We do this,

425
00:25:29,762 --> 00:25:31,829
And then you
and I...

426
00:25:31,831 --> 00:25:33,264
We're finished.

427
00:25:33,266 --> 00:25:35,232
I've spent the last two weeks
trying to convince myself

428
00:25:35,234 --> 00:25:36,700
That we want
the same thing.

429
00:25:36,702 --> 00:25:38,602
We do.
No.

430
00:25:38,604 --> 00:25:40,671
I want a future.

431
00:25:40,673 --> 00:25:42,573
I want something that
I can build towards.

432
00:25:42,575 --> 00:25:43,841
You want a kingdom.

433
00:25:43,843 --> 00:25:46,310
This town needs
a leader.

434
00:25:47,946 --> 00:25:49,580
Not your kind.

435
00:25:51,249 --> 00:25:52,983
Made a few mistakes.

436
00:25:52,985 --> 00:25:55,653
But nobody loves this town
better than I do.

437
00:25:55,655 --> 00:25:58,188
No, you love power, jim.

438
00:25:58,190 --> 00:26:00,558
That's it.

439
00:26:00,560 --> 00:26:02,793
Now, we take down max,
and we are done.

440
00:26:02,795 --> 00:26:04,862
And then I am gonna do
whatever I have to do

441
00:26:04,864 --> 00:26:07,565
To make sure that I knock
you off of your throne.

442
00:26:17,609 --> 00:26:19,143
Norrie? Where's joe?

443
00:26:19,145 --> 00:26:20,611
I don't know.

444
00:26:20,613 --> 00:26:22,980
He went to go talk to julia
and hasn't come back.

445
00:26:23,949 --> 00:26:25,349
Well, he must still
be there, right?

446
00:26:25,351 --> 00:26:27,651
He wouldn't try to come
back in this storm.

447
00:26:27,653 --> 00:26:28,986
We barely made it ourselves.

448
00:26:28,988 --> 00:26:30,287
Yeah, that was so weird.

449
00:26:30,289 --> 00:26:31,655
It came out of nowhere.

450
00:26:32,624 --> 00:26:34,058
Yeah, maybe not.

451
00:26:35,727 --> 00:26:36,727
Hey, guys.

452
00:26:36,729 --> 00:26:38,596
Joe! Where have you been?

453
00:26:38,598 --> 00:26:40,297
Where's julia?
She got shot.
What?

454
00:26:40,299 --> 00:26:41,899
Yeah,
in the chest.

455
00:26:41,901 --> 00:26:43,601
And then she died
for a minute,

456
00:26:43,603 --> 00:26:45,035
But she's gonna
be okay.

457
00:26:45,037 --> 00:26:47,104
Barbie brought her back.

458
00:26:47,106 --> 00:26:48,272
It was incredible.

459
00:26:48,274 --> 00:26:49,907
Thank god.

460
00:26:49,909 --> 00:26:52,776
Guys...

461
00:26:52,778 --> 00:26:54,912
I think he might be the monarch.

462
00:26:54,914 --> 00:26:56,380
The tornado

463
00:26:56,382 --> 00:26:58,782
Went away right after
he finished sucking the air

464
00:26:58,784 --> 00:27:00,317
Out of her chest,
it was...
Ew.

465
00:27:00,319 --> 00:27:03,754
No, that's not why
the storm stopped.

466
00:27:03,756 --> 00:27:05,089
What?

467
00:27:07,325 --> 00:27:09,627
It stopped because
I decided to come back.

468
00:27:10,395 --> 00:27:11,962
Okay...

469
00:27:11,964 --> 00:27:14,231
Look, something started it,

470
00:27:14,233 --> 00:27:15,866
And something stopped it.

471
00:27:17,369 --> 00:27:18,836
But what do we do now?

472
00:27:20,205 --> 00:27:22,973
we need to go to the dome.

473
00:27:26,811 --> 00:27:28,412
The big dome.

474
00:27:31,683 --> 00:27:32,683
Right.

475
00:27:32,685 --> 00:27:35,219
If these stars
are really us,

476
00:27:35,221 --> 00:27:38,288
Then we have to go to
the same spot on the big dome.

477
00:27:38,290 --> 00:27:40,758
Under the
north star...

478
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:43,961
Due north...

479
00:27:43,963 --> 00:27:46,130
That's right around
the bollingwood bridge.

480
00:27:46,132 --> 00:27:48,365
And then what?

481
00:27:48,367 --> 00:27:50,968
I don't know.

482
00:27:50,970 --> 00:27:53,370
Stuff happened when
we touched it together.

483
00:27:53,372 --> 00:27:54,938
Okay.

484
00:27:54,940 --> 00:27:57,141
So... The four of us

485
00:27:57,143 --> 00:27:59,176
Need to do the exact same thing.

486
00:28:00,111 --> 00:28:01,445
Angie:
Enough guessing.

487
00:28:02,782 --> 00:28:04,314
The dome owes us some answers.

488
00:28:11,423 --> 00:28:12,923
So what's the plan?

489
00:28:12,925 --> 00:28:14,925
We March right in

490
00:28:14,927 --> 00:28:16,427
And let her
ambush us?

491
00:28:16,429 --> 00:28:18,696
We're not going
in the front door.

492
00:28:18,698 --> 00:28:21,265
Julia showed me another way
the day the missile hit.

493
00:28:21,267 --> 00:28:22,700
What are
you doing?

494
00:28:22,702 --> 00:28:24,301
I'm giving us a way out.

495
00:28:26,871 --> 00:28:28,205
It's just an alarm clock.

496
00:28:28,207 --> 00:28:29,873
The hell do we need
an alarm for?

497
00:28:31,143 --> 00:28:33,177
just in case.

498
00:28:44,456 --> 00:28:46,123
Let's go.

499
00:28:54,499 --> 00:28:57,935
Phil:
Julia's car is gone.

500
00:28:58,903 --> 00:29:01,271
I guess barbie took her.

501
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:04,041
Oh, god.

502
00:29:04,043 --> 00:29:05,809
I didn't think he could
ever go this far.

503
00:29:10,181 --> 00:29:11,849
How well do you know barbie?

504
00:29:12,784 --> 00:29:14,418
I don't think anybody knows him.

505
00:29:14,420 --> 00:29:16,053
Julia does.

506
00:29:16,055 --> 00:29:17,454
Or thought she did.

507
00:29:17,456 --> 00:29:21,458
Peter shumway...

508
00:29:21,460 --> 00:29:22,960
He was in deep.

509
00:29:22,962 --> 00:29:24,461
He bet the house.

510
00:29:24,463 --> 00:29:27,164
Literally.

511
00:29:27,166 --> 00:29:28,465
The house.

512
00:29:28,467 --> 00:29:30,901
And lost.

513
00:29:30,903 --> 00:29:32,803
And barbie was
the collection agent.

514
00:29:32,805 --> 00:29:35,038
Wasn't too polite
about it, either.

515
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:36,774
Do you really think...

516
00:29:36,776 --> 00:29:38,842
If barbie killed peter...

517
00:29:41,479 --> 00:29:43,881
And then julia found out.

518
00:29:58,097 --> 00:30:01,932
Would you just shut your mouth
for once?

519
00:30:04,570 --> 00:30:06,837
Hello, boys.

520
00:30:08,339 --> 00:30:10,407
Keep walking.

521
00:30:20,852 --> 00:30:22,853
That's all they
were packing, boss.

522
00:30:22,855 --> 00:30:24,354
Jim killed my
mother, barbie.

523
00:30:26,357 --> 00:30:27,457
I don't suppose

524
00:30:27,459 --> 00:30:29,593
He told you that,
did he?

525
00:30:31,863 --> 00:30:33,597
You two are
just the same.

526
00:30:33,599 --> 00:30:35,966
I don't think so.
You and me, though...

527
00:30:35,968 --> 00:30:38,535
Well, that's
a different story.

528
00:30:38,537 --> 00:30:40,971
We were good together.

529
00:30:40,973 --> 00:30:43,073
No, we were never good.

530
00:30:43,075 --> 00:30:46,844
You paid me, I did a job,
that's it.

531
00:30:46,846 --> 00:30:48,579
Well, it's a good thing
you're handsome, brother,

532
00:30:48,581 --> 00:30:50,547
Because you sure are
thick sometimes.

533
00:30:50,549 --> 00:30:52,416
What do you mean?

534
00:30:52,418 --> 00:30:55,319
I mean, I'm giving you
a chance...

535
00:30:55,321 --> 00:30:57,020
To live.

536
00:30:57,022 --> 00:30:59,056
What, with you?

537
00:31:00,358 --> 00:31:02,559
Max, you shot julia.

538
00:31:02,561 --> 00:31:04,561
She was never right
for you, anyway.

539
00:31:04,563 --> 00:31:06,496
You're the one
who's not right, max.

540
00:31:16,174 --> 00:31:18,342
I had plans for you.

541
00:31:22,247 --> 00:31:24,181
I trusted you...

542
00:31:24,183 --> 00:31:26,383
And you screwed me over.

543
00:31:28,319 --> 00:31:30,387
You're no different from him...

544
00:31:30,389 --> 00:31:32,456
Or from anyone else
in this town.

545
00:31:32,458 --> 00:31:33,590
Look who's talking.

546
00:31:33,592 --> 00:31:36,026
No, that is
not true, jim!

547
00:31:36,028 --> 00:31:37,427
I am nothing like you!

548
00:31:37,429 --> 00:31:39,396
I am a survivor!

549
00:31:42,066 --> 00:31:44,001
If you have plans
to be somewhere,

550
00:31:44,003 --> 00:31:48,405
Then someone is going
to be <i>very</i> disappointed.

551
00:31:53,946 --> 00:31:55,312
Barbie:
Get down!

552
00:32:02,987 --> 00:32:05,622
Now we are all leaving.

553
00:32:05,624 --> 00:32:08,926
Let's go. Go.

554
00:32:10,061 --> 00:32:11,495
Julia's here,
but barbie's gone.

555
00:32:11,497 --> 00:32:14,064
They said that he
took off with big jim.

556
00:32:14,066 --> 00:32:15,565
Could be
at the cement factory.

557
00:32:15,567 --> 00:32:17,134
Max set up a fight club there.

558
00:32:17,136 --> 00:32:19,069
Heard people say they lost
money on barbie yesterday.

559
00:32:21,606 --> 00:32:22,606
Get out.

560
00:32:22,608 --> 00:32:24,942
Come on. Linda,

561
00:32:24,944 --> 00:32:26,977
You cannot do this
by yourself, man.

562
00:32:26,979 --> 00:32:28,946
You're not a cop, phil.

563
00:32:28,948 --> 00:32:30,547
I'll see you soon.

564
00:32:32,383 --> 00:32:34,418
You're stealing my car.

565
00:32:44,195 --> 00:32:45,429
I'll go get
our car.

566
00:32:45,431 --> 00:32:47,631
I'll take them
down to the station.

567
00:32:47,633 --> 00:32:50,033
You don't want
to do this, I promise.

568
00:32:50,035 --> 00:32:53,103
I already took care of your
little insurance policy.

569
00:32:53,105 --> 00:32:55,672
you have no idea.

570
00:33:03,414 --> 00:33:04,648
It's over.

571
00:33:17,161 --> 00:33:19,563
What the hell did you do?!

572
00:33:19,565 --> 00:33:22,366
As long as max
is breathing,

573
00:33:22,368 --> 00:33:23,533
She's a threat.

574
00:33:23,535 --> 00:33:26,603
Now she's not.

575
00:33:26,605 --> 00:33:29,172
And neither are you.

576
00:33:37,715 --> 00:33:40,484
linda:
Barbie, put that weapon down!

577
00:33:40,486 --> 00:33:42,285
Put it down now!

578
00:33:42,287 --> 00:33:43,720
Big jim:
Linda, thank god!

579
00:33:43,722 --> 00:33:45,555
He's gone nuts!

580
00:33:45,557 --> 00:33:48,025
Big jim:
He killed 'em!

581
00:33:48,027 --> 00:33:50,060
First he cuffed 'em, and then
he shot 'em in the head!

582
00:33:50,062 --> 00:33:52,229
I was next!

583
00:33:53,731 --> 00:33:55,766
Back up, barbie.

584
00:33:55,768 --> 00:33:57,667
Put the weapon down.

585
00:34:12,483 --> 00:34:14,751
Put your hands
behind your back.

586
00:34:14,753 --> 00:34:16,620
You killed your last victim.

587
00:34:16,622 --> 00:34:18,121
Spread your legs apart.

588
00:34:18,123 --> 00:34:19,689
You're done.

589
00:34:19,691 --> 00:34:22,125
Linda, I'm telling you...

590
00:34:28,466 --> 00:34:30,500
Stop, or I'll shoot!

591
00:34:30,502 --> 00:34:32,736
Shoot that
son of a bitch!

592
00:34:47,351 --> 00:34:49,286
Big jim:
<i>Am I set?</i>

593
00:34:49,288 --> 00:34:50,787
Two secs.
Almost there.

594
00:34:50,789 --> 00:34:52,756
Hey, jim?
Yeah?

595
00:34:52,758 --> 00:34:54,191
I heard something
today.

596
00:34:54,193 --> 00:34:56,293
From the outside.

597
00:34:56,295 --> 00:34:57,761
It was about barbie.

598
00:34:57,763 --> 00:35:00,263
What are you talking about?

599
00:35:00,265 --> 00:35:03,266
It was the military.
They know he's in here.

600
00:35:03,268 --> 00:35:06,636
Tell me exactly what they said.

601
00:35:06,638 --> 00:35:10,107
They said that he's the one.

602
00:35:10,109 --> 00:35:12,442
The one that they've been
looking for.

603
00:35:13,411 --> 00:35:15,178
Turn it on.

604
00:35:17,548 --> 00:35:19,316
This is jim rennie.

605
00:35:19,318 --> 00:35:21,151
I'm sorry to report

606
00:35:21,153 --> 00:35:24,287
That this has been a very dark
day in chester's mill.

607
00:35:24,289 --> 00:35:27,290
I need all citizens
to be aware and vigilant.

608
00:35:27,292 --> 00:35:30,560
Today, maxine seagrave
and her business associate

609
00:35:30,562 --> 00:35:35,599
Otto aguilar were murdered,
shot execution style.

610
00:35:35,601 --> 00:35:37,501
Many of you may have known max.

611
00:35:37,503 --> 00:35:41,538
She was a reputable
businesswoman from westlake.

612
00:35:41,540 --> 00:35:46,176
In addition, an attempt was made
on the life of julia shumway.

613
00:35:46,178 --> 00:35:47,844
She suffered a gunshot
to the chest

614
00:35:47,846 --> 00:35:49,446
And may not survive.

615
00:35:49,448 --> 00:35:52,182
There was also an attempt
made on my own life.

616
00:35:52,184 --> 00:35:54,451
One person is responsible
for all this...

617
00:35:54,453 --> 00:35:58,555
Dale "barbie" barbara.

618
00:35:58,557 --> 00:36:01,324
A warrant has been issued
for his arrest.

619
00:36:01,326 --> 00:36:03,193
<i>He's been charged</i>
<i>with the attempted murders</i>

620
00:36:03,195 --> 00:36:04,594
<i>Of mrs. Shumway and myself.</i>

621
00:36:04,596 --> 00:36:06,796
He's also been charged
with the murders

622
00:36:06,798 --> 00:36:09,499
Of max seagrave, otto aguilar,

623
00:36:09,501 --> 00:36:12,802
And ms. Seagraves mother,
agatha.

624
00:36:12,804 --> 00:36:14,704
Barbie is on the run.

625
00:36:14,706 --> 00:36:19,776
And for those reasons, I'm
declaring a state of emergency.

626
00:36:19,778 --> 00:36:22,812
This senseless violence
will not be tolerated.

627
00:36:22,814 --> 00:36:25,482
What barbie did
is not who we are.

628
00:36:25,484 --> 00:36:27,250
Even now. Especially now.

629
00:36:27,252 --> 00:36:29,786
<i>When barbie is taken</i>
<i>into custody,</i>

630
00:36:29,788 --> 00:36:31,688
<i>He'll be given a fair trial.</i>

631
00:36:31,690 --> 00:36:38,428
The people,
will seek the death penalty.

632
00:36:40,364 --> 00:36:42,265
Angie:
Any bets on what will happen

633
00:36:42,267 --> 00:36:43,900
When the four
of us touch it?

634
00:36:43,902 --> 00:36:46,303
All I want is answers.

635
00:36:46,305 --> 00:36:50,240
Not a seizure
or riddle.

636
00:36:50,242 --> 00:36:51,708
Just answers.

637
00:36:57,248 --> 00:36:59,449
All right,

638
00:36:59,451 --> 00:37:01,818
Whatever happens,

639
00:37:01,820 --> 00:37:03,820
Don't let go.

640
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:51,901
♪

641
00:37:57,475 --> 00:37:58,842
Dad?

642
00:38:25,870 --> 00:38:27,070
Dad!

643
00:38:38,783 --> 00:38:40,817
Junior.

644
00:38:50,795 --> 00:38:52,028
No!

645
00:38:57,335 --> 00:38:59,402
Dad!

646
00:39:01,639 --> 00:39:03,707
I gotta go find my dad.

647
00:39:06,077 --> 00:39:07,610
Wait!

648
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:11,114
Did we all see the same thing?

649
00:39:11,116 --> 00:39:12,449
Big jim?

650
00:39:12,451 --> 00:39:13,583
Yeah.

651
00:39:13,585 --> 00:39:14,984
What the hell was that?

652
00:39:14,986 --> 00:39:17,554
I-I thought we were coming here
for answers.

653
00:39:17,556 --> 00:39:19,389
We were, joe.

654
00:39:19,391 --> 00:39:21,591
I think that was it.

655
00:39:21,593 --> 00:39:23,026
What was it?

656
00:39:23,028 --> 00:39:25,895
Maybe the dome's coming down.

657
00:39:25,897 --> 00:39:27,931
First...

658
00:39:27,933 --> 00:39:30,467
Big jim has to die.

659
00:39:31,969 --> 00:39:34,771
And I think
we're supposed to do it.

660
00:39:34,773 --> 00:39:35,839
